    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>TO MONTREAL BY TRAIN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sarah Sloane letter on Aric Chen's October 22 travel article on 36-hour visit to Montreal; recommends taking train from New York to Montreal</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I am dumbfounded that in ''36 Hours: Montreal'' (Oct. 22), Aric Chen didn't mention the train from New York to Montreal. Seven hours by car? Why in the world would someone do such a thing when there is an available and convenient train? Not to mention, in this era of global warming, the train is the least polluting form of transportation per rider.</p>
        <p>Sarah A. Sloane  Farmington, Me.</p>
      </block>
